description.4: Domino and Shatterstar learn of the technology developed to create self-aware robots! Meanwhile, it is revealed that Agenda Tomorrow is preparing to build a Nimrod…
description.8: The Midnight Sons confront Strange over his bungling of Salome. Wong and Imei locate Vincent Stevens.
description.10: Donyell Taylor joins the team as Bandit as the New Warriors are pulled into a timeline-crossing battle.
description.12: Still reeling from the death of his parents, Peter struggles to find purpose as Spider-Man. Carrion faces his own guilt from past sins, while Shriek flies off the handle! Who will pay the price?
description.13: Black Knight discovers that Proctor is his parallel Earth counterpart. After realizing that her madness may be incurable, Sersi banishes herself to a pocket dimension. Plus, Ute the Watcher gets involved in the Avengers' fray with the Gatherers!
description.14: The sinister Senyaka has murderous plans for ship captain Lee Forrester, and the only thing that stands between them is Cable! It's a showdown in the wilderness- but can Cable and Lee make it out alive?
description.17: A race between brothers! Lord Tantalus orders one of his sons to kidnap a renowned geneticist, but his other son will do whatever it takes to stop him! Which brother will end up on top?
description.19: Venom is alone and at his weakest point, so Mace sees an opportunity to strike! But as the mysterious mercenary and the savage symbiote clash, a sinister group lurks in the shadows...
description.20: Daredevil and Captain America join forces to face off with the tech-based terrors known as System Crash! But when the battle takes a vicious turn, a surprising but welcome ally enters the fray- Danny Rand, the Iron Fist!
description.21: Zero frees Douglock from the Phalanx collective!
description.22: Rick Jones, the Hulk's oldest (and for a long time, only) friend, is tying the knot with Marlo Chandler! But the wedding gets cut off by an unexpected guest - the devious Mephisto, who wants nothing less than Marlo's soul!
description.23: While Tony decides to recreate Stark Industries as an ethical company, the Mandarin awakens, and Vor/Tex moves on to the next phase of his plan.
description.25: Ice and Microchip attempt to spring Frank Castle from prison!
description.27: Thor discovers Don Blake in a cave on Wundagore! The two enter battle side-by-side to save Jane Foster from Karnivore!
description.30: They've survived the past - now onto the future! The FF find themselves on a destroyed future Earth - a destruction that they are destined to cause! But who is the villain obsessed with killing every Reed Richards in the multiverse? And what is the Watcher's role in all these events?
description.31: While Gambit, Yukio, and Storm battle the Phalanx, the others must contend with a host of problems back at the mansion. Bobby, despite having transformed into his ice form, has yet to wake up. And Professor X attempts to cure Sabretooth's bloodlust.
description.33: Sabretooth reveals to Rogue Gambit's history while living in Paris. What will Rogue be upset by - the fact that Gambit had a clandestine affair, or that he let a lover die in order to save his brother?
description.39: A gang of interplanetary thieves steal'See-Threepio'and'Artoo-Detoo'from the'Pitareeze family, and take the'droids'to'Kalarba's'moon,'Indobok. The droids meet a nefarious character from their past, and realize that their troubles have just begun!
description.43: Freed from mind control, the Avengers join Warlock in confronting the senator that hypnotized them! But when Senator Kyle Munson reveals his true form, Adam must contend with…the Man-Beast!
description.45: Wirehead enters the game! This techno-menace thinks the whole world is a video game, and Daredevil is his final boss! Can the Man Without Fear take down the delusional hacker before it's game over?
description.47: The Hulk has faced down some of the most dangerous beings in all of creation. He's survived cosmic events of cataclysmic proportions. He is, quite simply, the STRONGEST THERE IS. But now, the Hulk must somehow endure his most bizarre challenge yet - Rick Jones' bachelor party!?
description.48: Tony gets in the middle of a dispute between Thunderstrike and the New Warriors. Plus, Iron Man faces down Hulk!
description.50: The Punisher is captured and put into prison where he is forced into servitude.
description.52: Thor reflects on his history and past battles.
description.55: It's the Fantastic Four vs....the Fantastic Four! And if facing their past selves wasn't enough, the FF has another challenge waiting - the Avengers of the past join the battle!
description.56: Storm and Yukio versus the Phalanx!
description.61: Rictor, Domino and Cable head to Guadalajara, Mexico to confront Rictor's family in light of their recent troubles….meanwhile, Magma is torn up over her true identity and breaks some hurtful news to Empath.
description.64: The “other” Doctor Strange remains missing. And, the Sorcerer Supreme versus Vengeance!
description.66: A mission of revenge! Spider-Man embarks for Kraven's mansion to take down the villain responsible for destroying his family- the Chameleon.
description.67: The Avengers reassemble following Sersi's destruction of Avengers Mansion. Has their teammate fallen outside their grasp of control? Plus, Sersi nearly loses it when she discovers the true source of Proctor's powers.
description.68: Led on a wild goose chase and surrounded with no escape, Cable responds the only way he knows how- by waging a one-man war on the Acolytes inside their own base! But can even he fend off the villainous mutants and stop Omega Red's plans at the same time?
description.75: Anath-Na Mut merges with his love Meryet to become an even deadlier incarnation of the Sphinx.
description.78: The Snakeroot returns! The sinister order has resurrected an old foe of Daredevil and Elektra, one who won't rest until they're put down for good! Guest-starring the Master of Kung Fu, Shang-Chi!
description.80: Venom vs. Mace! The enigmatic bounty hunter has his sights set on the symbiote, but Venom certainly won't go down without a fight!
description.84: The Infinity Watch throws down with the Avengers! Can Adam and his friends find a way to free Earth's Mightiest Heroes from their brainwashing?
description.88: System Crash strikes! The target: The Staten Island Ferry! And the Avengers taking over the rescue means Daredevil has to take his investigation "underground". Meanwhile, Captain America does some investigating of his own!
description.90: Hulk, Surfer, and the Starjammers at last catch up with Trauma...and come face to face with his leader, the powerful Armageddon! But as far as Hulk is concerned, there's only two options for them: give up, or get smashed!
description.91: After rescuing Night Thrasher, Iron Man must do battle with Thunderstrike.
description.92: Steel Raven and Typhoid Mary team-up to 'punish' men who have abused their wives. Typhoid's damaging shrink is exposed. Mary, and all her personalities, make a vow to protect the rights of women!
description.93: Alex Ross brings a new perspective to the death of Gwen Stacy, launching a haunting, realistic portrayal of one of Marvel's most devastating events.
description.94: The Punisher visits a tropical island to take on a drug kingpin, and he's not going to hold back.
description.96: Vizier, Balder and Sif break Odin's mandate and sneak into Migard, where they make some shocking discoveries about Thor, Ymir, and Surtur!
description.99: The FF learns that Reed may yet be alive - but stranded in another time! When they decide to investigate for themselves, their first stop brings them face to face with a blast from the past.

1.text: Our Rebel heroes will have to face a regular rogues' gallery of Star Wars rapscallions and wretches: Darth Vader, Raskar, Skorr, and even that most nefarious of bounty hunters, Boba Fett!

2.text: Five years after being pulled into the future, Scott and Jean adopt new names, now going by Slym and Redd Dayspring. But when a mysterious stranger overhears the couple speaking an “olde English” tongue, will their past collide with their present?

3.text: Between snarky barbs, War Machine and Deathlok exchange blows. Why has the cyborg confronted James Rhodes? And what technology does War Machine possess that Deathlok must have?

4.text: Domino and Shatterstar learn of the technology developed to create self-aware robots! Meanwhile, it is revealed that Agenda Tomorrow is preparing to build a Nimrod…

5.text: A Shi’ar envoy more or less kidnaps all the X-Men present – in this case Xavier, Storm, Forge and Jubilee – as they are expected to appear at an official royal function on the recently annexed Kree homeworld, Hala!

8.text: The Midnight Sons confront Strange over his bungling of Salome. Wong and Imei locate Vincent Stevens.

11.text: When Xi'an and the X-Men get a desperate message from Krystalin, they decide to journey to New Mexico. They arrive at what appears to be a base and discover Master Zhao and...more X-Men?

15.text: Deadpool barely escapes with his life after duking it out against Malachi’s demons. Will the Secret Defenders be able to subdue Malachi before it’s too late? Shadowoman uses her newly bolstered powers, impressing Deadpool and teammate alike!

16.text: Legacy is intent on destroying Nitro, the villain responsible for killing his father, Captain Marvel. What follows is a worthy battle of galactic proportion! But will Legacy be able to take Nitro’s life?

17.text: A race between brothers! Lord Tantalus orders one of his sons to kidnap a renowned geneticist, but his other son will do whatever it takes to stop him! Which brother will end up on top?

18.text: Protégé receives final judgment from a supreme being!

19.text: Venom is alone and at his weakest point, so Mace sees an opportunity to strike! But as the mysterious mercenary and the savage symbiote clash, a sinister group lurks in the shadows...

25.text: Ice and Microchip attempt to spring Frank Castle from prison!

29.text: Strong Guy invites Random and Wolfsbane to meet his family. Malice takes control over Havok!

32.text: Is Wolverine…dying? Logan heads to Japan to get his affairs in order with Yukio, Amiko and the Silver Samurai.

33.text: Sabretooth reveals to Rogue Gambit's history while living in Paris. What will Rogue be upset by - the fact that Gambit had a clandestine affair, or that he let a lover die in order to save his brother?

36.text: What will be the future of the Nova Corps in the midst of “Time and Time Again”?

38.text: General Sharpe seeks retribution against Spider-Man (and the Daily Bugle). Flash Thompson faces a plot against his life!

41.text: After Lyla flies off the handle, and falls off the grid, Miguel discovers that all of Nueva York’s computers have gone off-line. What forces are behind this electrical failure? Gabe O’ Hara falls into trouble when he retreats into a virtual reality. Will Conchata be able to pull her son back to this world? Or will Gabe remain “plugged in” for life?

42.text: CAPTAIN AMERICA BOOK 3 The man impersonating Cap has gone too far! The real Cap is ready to stop the madness-but will he harm himself in the process?

43.text: Freed from mind control, the Avengers join Warlock in confronting the senator that hypnotized them! But when Senator Kyle Munson reveals his true form, Adam must contend with…the Man-Beast!

50.text: The Punisher is captured and put into prison where he is forced into servitude.

53.text: The Chameleon unleashes chaos when a busload of escaped convicts take to the streets of New York!

54.text: What is the “Polaris Plot”? Lorna Dane finds out in this incredible battle issue!

57.text: Having barely escaped Cyber, Wolverine heads to Muir Island. But Cyber is unshakeable and is still in pursuit of Logan. However, Logan's overtaxed healing factor sends him shock and Nightcrawler and Shadowcat must defend a weakend Wolverine against Cyber!

58.text: While the rest of the team are desperate to find them- Sam, Boomer, and Magma are stuck in a sick and twisted game by the Gamemaster. Will X-Force interrogating the Guthrie family be enough to save their teammates?

61.text: Rictor, Domino and Cable head to Guadalajara, Mexico to confront Rictor's family in light of their recent troubles….meanwhile, Magma is torn up over her true identity and breaks some hurtful news to Empath.

64.text: The “other” Doctor Strange remains missing. And, the Sorcerer Supreme versus Vengeance!

69.text: Jean Grey and Scott Summers, displaced to a timeline where Apocalypse rules all! Two millennia into the future, the X-couple must face a new reality without their powers. Their daughter, Rachel Summers, is the Mother Askani. Nathan, their son, has been infected by a techno-organic virus by Apocalypse. With the stakes high and the future dim, will Cyclops and Phoenix be able to withstand the Age of Apocalypse?

70.text: "Between Deathlok and a Hard Case" War Machine continues to battle the Advisor and Eda Arul. But before loose ends are tied up, Deathlok appears on the scene!

71.text: Han and the Rebels' recent adventures throughout the galaxy have not gone completely unnoticed by those interested in taking advantage of the easy money. In fairly short order, they meet up with an old foe who turns out to be a friend, and a couple of enemies, who will have a much greater role to play in Return of the Jedi. A series of adventures ultimately winds up with our heroes crash-landing on Hoth, searching for a treasure which may or may not exist.

72.text: The X-Men and the Freakshow discover a common enemy and Mama Hurricane gives Xi'an a very important gift!

73.text: A Special One-Shot! Learn the hidden origins of Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D.!

74.text: The true intention behind Brand’s ‘mutant serum’ is laid bare…placing Beast and his X-cohorts in grave danger! But with Spider-Man in tow, the Brand Corporation and Hobgoblin have much to fear…and to lose!

76.text: Sorcerer Supreme Doctor Strange enlists the help of Dr. Druid when a mystical threat approaches Earth. Will Earth’s most powerful mystics be able to defend the planet from the occult? Enter Malachi and the Shadowoman!

77.text: Ganymede of the Spinsterhood may be the key to defeating Tyrant. But will Terrax and Thanos be able to strike an alliance? Jack of Hearts finds himself falling for Ganymede, but her vows prevent love from taking hold. Will the two say no to Thanos…and live?

78.text: The Snakeroot returns! The sinister order has resurrected an old foe of Daredevil and Elektra, one who won't rest until they're put down for good! Guest-starring the Master of Kung Fu, Shang-Chi!

79.text: Overkill battles Hollywood…who's really Wonder Man from an alternate future!

80.text: Venom vs. Mace! The enigmatic bounty hunter has his sights set on the symbiote, but Venom certainly won't go down without a fight!

82.text: Spider-Man faces a sudden attack from the nefariously named Shadowforce! But X-Factor is on this case too...

83.text: A special What If? issue spotlighting Phoenix and Cyclops’s relationship! What if Jean Grey and Scott Summers had married earlier? What if the two had never fallen in love? And what if Jean had chosen Wolverine over Cyclops?

84.text: The Infinity Watch throws down with the Avengers! Can Adam and his friends find a way to free Earth's Mightiest Heroes from their brainwashing?

85.text: Lyla reacts in a jealous rage after Miguel and Dana share an intimate moment. Gabe retreats into virtual reality following his breakup with Kasey. Plus, a special story featuring Miguel O’ Hara from his school days! You’ll never believe what the X-Mansion of 2099 looks like!

86.text: FIGHTING CHANCE BOOK 2 Cap is in for the fight of his life, but it may cost him much more than that. FIGHTING CHANCE is heating up!

92.text: Steel Raven and Typhoid Mary team-up to ‘punish’ men who have abused their wives.  Typhoid’s damaging shrink is exposed. Mary, and all her personalities, make a vow to protect the rights of women!

93.text: Alex Ross brings a new perspective to the death of Gwen Stacy, launching a haunting, realistic portrayal of one of Marvel's most devastating events.

Even whilst enjoying some success upon getting his first book published, Photographer, Phil Sheldon, continues to be involved with the heroic "Marvels" and the villains of New York City. Don't miss out on this shocking conclusion to Marvels!

94.text: The Punisher visits a tropical island to take on a drug kingpin, and he's not going to hold back.

95.text: Peter Parker reconciles with the harsh reality that his “parents” were mere models created by the Chameleon.

98.text: Multiple Man has died, and Havok leaves the team in the wake of this tragedy.
